        public AsyncDatabaseReader(String executor,
                   AsyncQueue<E> output,
                   Database database,
                   Query<E> query)
        Creates a new instance that runs in the given executor, and produces items that match the given query from the given database into the given output queue.
        Parameters:
        executor - If null, uses the default executor.
        output - If null, creates a new queue.
        database - Can't be null.
        query - Can't be null.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given database or query is null.
